Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.44,0:27:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we dress the part and try to find the right person to help you. So we dress the part and try to find
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.46,0:27:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,coach. And I believe, I'm a big believer in coaching. There's all kinds of coaching going
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.04,0:27:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,now. It is a whole lifestyle of coaching. When enrollment do as the Romans do is something that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.57,0:27:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,many people seem to fail to learn. It's due to narcissism. They insist on doing it their way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.75,0:27:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're in Rome. The way to be successful is when you're in Rome, you do it as the Romans do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.88,0:27:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's fitting in, fitting in in a positive way with your culture, when in Rome, do as the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.15,0:28:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans do. Identify and evaluate the successful. Watch for subtleties. Watch for subtleties. Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.97,0:28:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say, class and rank and success is often reflected to others by very, very subtle,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.30,0:28:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,very,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.76,0:28:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,very subtle moves. A slight delay in a gesture of a split second has a totally different meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you move forward into the world of success, you'll find that subtleties have greater meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.04,0:28:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,than that which is overt. Whether you have a new Cadillac or not doesn't impress people that are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.75,0:28:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,very successful. Everybody's got a new Cadillac. No, you drive an 84 Cadillac, that's got class.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:29:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That class is an 84 Cadillac. Everybody can buy a new one. All right. Anyway, the subtleties of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.99,0:29:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,success, you pick up nuances. Nuances has to do with style and a way of being. And the way of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.82,0:29:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,being has to do with the degree of self-confidence as well as the training in the background of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.06,0:29:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,people. Some people are automatic. Some people are automatic. Some people are automatic. Some people are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.64,0:29:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic. Some people are automatic. Some people are automatic. Some people are automatic. Some people are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.79,0:29:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically polite. Automatically polite when it's not even required. You see, it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.70,0:29:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,required. You're automatically polite and considerate of others all the time because
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.25,0:29:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what you will become. You've become a considerate person towards others. And other
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.83,0:29:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,people pick up the subtle ways in which that considerateness is conveyed. Whether they're
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.07,0:29:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing you correctly, whether you can sit so that the sunlight is not in their eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.40,0:30:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,those are just examples of being considerate of others. Another one is to cut giant-sized projects
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.15,0:30:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,into bite-sized portions. Why? Because giant-sized projects are too dismaying. You know, you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.33,0:30:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have to house clean the whole house. You know, spring house cleaning. Now you've got a house
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.39,0:30:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaning the entire house. No, don't house clean. Do not house clean the whole house. Just do the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.50,0:30:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,upstairs bedroom, period.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.71,0:30:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay. You can do the upstairs bedroom, but house cleaning the whole house is heavy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.26,0:30:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,duty. So cut giant-sized projects into small portions. So after you do the small portions,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.92,0:30:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what's remaining is less than it was. I once dug a ditch a quarter of a mile long by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.95,0:30:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha. I did it by hand. Oh, God. It was a roadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.28,0:31:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a dirt roadway, and the rain would wash it out. So I had to dig a ditch on each side of this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.67,0:31:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,road to run the water off. Otherwise, the road was always getting washed off. Well, it was out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.60,0:31:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,woods. It went right through some very heavy, heavy woods. There's no way to get machinery in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.54,0:31:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there, and I don't think I had machinery in those years. So I decided, well, I'll just dig it by
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.15,0:31:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,hand. So I got a shovel, and I started digging the ditch on this side by hand, and then I
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.34,0:31:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,dug a little bit on this side by hand, and I said, well, I'll just dig 15 feet a day. So I dug
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.76,0:31:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,six feet, and then I dug another six feet, and I said, oh, hell, this ain't so bad. So I dig another
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.50,0:31:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,15 feet. Before you knew it, I dug 30 feet. Wow. Well, so I said, yesterday, I dug 30 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.50,0:31:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So today, I'll do 45 feet. So the next day, I did 60 feet. In a matter of time, I dug this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.29,0:31:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,quarter of a mile long ditch.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.72,0:32:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All by myself, with no mechanical tools or anything. If somebody said to you, can you dig a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.11,0:32:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,quarter of a mile ditch, I'd say, I don't think so. I'm not a mesomorph. I'm an ectomorph, you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.46,0:32:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,know. We don't dig ditches, ectomorphs. We think about it. We think about it and call the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.90,0:32:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mesomorphs, and they come in and do it, you know. And the endomorphs watch the whole project.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.04,0:32:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So we uplift other people by that which we have become. And our vision, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.36,0:32:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by sharing that which we are, we're sharing your aura. Now, within your aura is much that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.50,0:32:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,learned in this world. Within your world is the nonverbal. Within your aura is much of the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.07,0:33:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nonverbal, which you cannot share. You don't have enough time to sit down and describe to everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.74,0:33:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you've ever known about life in a linear way. The total collectiveness of your entitled life and all
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.74,0:33:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the wisdom and experience of it exists as an energy, as an energy field. So when you share that which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.55,0:33:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you have become with others, they pick up the energy field of all that knowingness. That's how it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.26,0:33:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that the guru, the spiritual teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.89,0:33:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,transmits enlightenment via an energy field. So it's the aura of the teacher has within itself
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.66,0:33:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective wisdom throughout all of time. There is no amount of world time in which all
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.52,0:34:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of this could be laid out in a linear lecture, intelligent class kind of a format. You could
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.24,0:34:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,extract some principles from it, but the principles are only basic principles. So the way to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.28,0:34:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,form an enlightenment is instantaneous. From the energy field of the teacher then, it radiates forth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.67,0:34:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy field. That field has within it the total knowingness of all that you need to become
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.51,0:34:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened, which is not really describable. It means becomingness, becomingness. Becomingness of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.78,0:34:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity within and becoming estándar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.84,0:34:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,one with that divinity in all of its expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.03,0:34:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we transmit to others without any verbalization,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.98,0:34:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,without any formality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.59,0:34:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you ride the subway,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.32,0:34:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you're influencing all the people in that subway train.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.28,0:35:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When you stand on the corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.55,0:35:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you're influencing everything around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.09,0:35:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The openness then, your own openness to awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.25,0:35:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting experiment was done recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.78,0:35:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the world's greatest violinists,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.01,0:35:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where this was reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.51,0:35:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget his name too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.59,0:35:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, one of the world's greatest violinists,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.57,0:35:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to know his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.73,0:35:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell it to me later when I go to bed tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.25,0:35:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the subway station,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.05,0:35:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he was always done an experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.44,0:35:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,some, I forget what university.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.07,0:35:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He was done his experiment by a university.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.67,0:35:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, one of the world's greatest violinists
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.71,0:35:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,played in the subway in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.55,0:35:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, so he's playing in there
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.61,0:35:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and occasional people would come over and give him a dollar
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.92,0:35:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody would give him $5 and somebody would give him 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.67,0:35:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knew who he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.88,0:36:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He was anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.75,0:36:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's this anonymous violin player.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.63,0:36:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, he collected, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.25,0:36:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,$50 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.63,0:36:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single person recognized who he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.19,0:36:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one single person recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.55,0:36:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that one of the world's greatest, most famous violinists
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.65,0:36:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was doing, he was doing, you know, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.86,0:36:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he was doing it for free in a subway station.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.50,0:36:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So this has to do with framing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.96,0:36:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the framing, people could not see the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.78,0:36:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had said one of the world's greatest violinists
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.05,0:36:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will be in the subway station,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.73,0:36:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody would be rushing down and recognize who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.53,0:36:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.13,0:36:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So framing, it isn't just the truth of anything that you say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.82,0:36:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way in which it is held
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.23,0:36:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and presented to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.30,0:36:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way in which you hold
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.28,0:36:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all that you have learned in life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.40,0:36:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and hold it for others,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.71,0:37:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you become not only what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.38,0:37:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but how that is held.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.59,0:37:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How you hold who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.09,0:37:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How you frame who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.15,0:37:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you frame yourself as thankful gift of God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.36,0:37:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.15,0:37:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then you are a gift of God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.32,0:37:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.88,0:37:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you frame yourself as a miserable worm,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.78,0:37:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,then you are a miserable worm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.63,0:37:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you become what you say you will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.51,0:37:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want all of us to own the infinite dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.65,0:37:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which we are for the sake of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.96,0:37:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.50,0:37:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.48,0:37:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hold out our hands to God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.05,0:37:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and own the divinity within us,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.90,0:37:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is within us is the source of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.09,0:37:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to the salvation of all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.38,0:37:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for which we thank Thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.25,0:37:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.71,0:38:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, we've all owned who we really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.69,0:38:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to signal something?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.26,0:38:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.71,0:38:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.57,0:38:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.75,0:38:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.57,0:38:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.55,0:38:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time for lunch, people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.28,0:38:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was interested in saving the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.90,0:38:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, well, you're saving the world already,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.51,0:38:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's why you can have lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.05,0:38:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.15,0:38:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What time?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.44,0:38:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume at 2 o'clock, then, after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.90,0:38:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What time?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.82,0:38:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.59,0:38:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,2 o'clock, we'll meet again for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.78,0:38:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.67,0:38:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.42,0:38:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we've got 101, so we'd better move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.69,0:39:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We said identify with a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.86,0:39:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, we came out here to California.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.05,0:39:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually a whole group of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.09,0:39:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole group of us, a dozen or so people all together,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.63,0:39:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,dressed apart because,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.94,0:39:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,part of life is unconsciously role-playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.11,0:39:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We often, you know, act and behave the way we believe that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.71,0:39:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you can do that with hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.90,0:39:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell people that they are something or not something,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.09,0:39:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will immediately begin to act and behave that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.92,0:39:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're afraid of everybody, and you don't have much confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.73,0:39:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person will instantly become hesitant and self,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.19,0:39:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and deprecating, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.59,0:39:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned this morning the value of a coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.53,0:39:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody that can give you some valid feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.51,0:39:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days of Christianity, you had a confessor.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.03,0:40:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday afternoon, you went to confession,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.30,0:40:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then your confessor would give you so many Hail Marys
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.98,0:40:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and Our Fathers to say repentance,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.53,0:40:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but he would also give you some kind of a feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.19,0:40:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to spend more time at your studies
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.17,0:40:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and more time being nice to your mother or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.46,0:40:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When in Rome, you want to blend in, do as the Romans do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.05,0:40:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And many social faux pas are just the failure to recognize that edict
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.46,0:40:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because it shows respect for a different culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.17,0:40:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in a different culture, it's respectful to respect their culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.94,0:40:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's okay to wear something on your head, wear it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.73,0:40:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it's not, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.90,0:40:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, try to blend in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.50,0:40:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next thing is to identify and evaluate people who are successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.71,0:40:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Become like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.57,0:41:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Adopt what positive aspects they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.05,0:41:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're reflecting, certainly, something positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.78,0:41:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we mentioned a few people,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.48,0:41:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course, one of their great successes is due to the fact that they're enthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.75,0:41:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're enthusiastic about their ventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.98,0:41:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in trying to, when in Rome, do as the Romans do,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.34,0:41:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,watch for subtleties, subtle little communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.36,0:41:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The other next thing you can do is take a giant-sized project,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.44,0:41:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I mentioned this morning, cut it down to bite-sized portions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.21,0:41:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, I dug a ditch on both sides of the road for a quarter of a mile by my lonesome
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.63,0:41:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by just doing six feet a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.92,0:41:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I said, six feet, that's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.21,0:41:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I could do 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.55,0:41:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I do 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.63,0:41:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next day, I do 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.19,0:41:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we benefit from the confidence of that which we have accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.19,0:41:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.92,0:42:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Activate the ego ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.65,0:42:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, Freud identified the ego ideal as really,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.21,0:42:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an aspect of the conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.55,0:42:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the ego ideal is people that we identify with.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.13,0:42:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, very often, the parents are supposed,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.69,0:42:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they're supposed to serve in that function.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.34,0:42:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I always wanted to become as affectionate and sociable and likable as my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.90,0:42:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was my ego ideal of sociability.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.01,0:42:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When my father sat down to the piano, a whole crowd would form around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.32,0:42:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,People would start to sing in joviality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.42,0:42:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was his sociability and good-naturedness became an ego ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.26,0:42:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To be good-natured, to be sociable,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.11,0:43:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to put your arms around your brother and zing-zongs together.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.78,0:43:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the ego ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.09,0:43:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get energy and inspiration in surges.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.32,0:43:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you learn to take advantage of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.84,0:43:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of dismissing them and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.65,0:43:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I'll do that later today at 4 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.01,0:43:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When the urge comes on you at 8 in the morning to complete a certain project,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.92,0:43:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I found that it saves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.19,0:43:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It saves a lot of expenditure of time, thought, and energy to sit down and do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.15,0:43:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So 150 or 101 ways to success was partly the result of inspirational urges.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.57,0:43:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And, for instance, it's not what you do, but it's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.07,0:43:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it was an inspirational urge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.23,0:43:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.67,0:43:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It just became aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.94,0:43:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not what you do, it's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.75,0:43:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.34,0:43:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The next trick is to always have a notepad.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.32,0:43:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a notepad next to your bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.46,0:44:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all the wonderful insights and wonderful phrases and thoughts you've had just before you go to bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.17,0:44:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, I'll remember that in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.53,0:44:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the morning, you forgot what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.53,0:44:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I found always have a note next to the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.21,0:44:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So part of today's lecture is due to a notepad next to the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.01,0:44:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.38,0:44:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.90,0:44:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a notepad next to your bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.21,0:44:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To be rational.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.11,0:44:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask, what does the world value, want, or need?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.32,0:44:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then try to supply it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.65,0:44:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the world really value?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.80,0:44:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it really want?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.67,0:44:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it really need?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.80,0:44:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And does your idea fit it or supply it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.65,0:44:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are ways to guarantee success, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.44,0:44:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Capitalize on frenetic energy surges.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.15,0:44:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while, you'll get just a frenetic surge of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.32,0:44:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.38,0:45:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is to capitalize on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.88,0:45:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to put it aside and say, I'll do it later when I have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.59,0:45:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At 3 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at 3 o'clock, that energy surge is not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.03,0:45:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of times, you know, I'd still do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.90,0:45:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump out of bed at 3 in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.17,0:45:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd go into my study and I'd write a few significant words on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.82,0:45:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'd go back to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.17,0:45:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next morning, it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.88,0:45:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I've learned from experience to write it down when it's hot in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.32,0:45:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's a hot topic in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.44,0:45:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the morning, you won't be that enthused.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.13,0:45:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you may want to remember, what the hell was that bright idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.25,0:45:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Gabe just came over to me and gave me a synoptic condensation of something I was going to say today.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.75,0:45:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't remember what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.59,0:45:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it, Gabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.76,0:45:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Word to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.73,0:45:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.46,0:45:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,ARP.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.88,0:46:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ARK?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.82,0:46:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,ARP.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.36,0:46:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,ARP.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.67,0:46:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,ARP.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.84,0:46:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was a mnemonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.15,0:46:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,For Donald Trump, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.15,0:46:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,ARP.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.73,0:46:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember what ARP stood for, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.36,0:46:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a hell of a good idea at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.19,0:46:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you wonder what makes him run.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.92,0:46:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already got more millions than he could ever spend or utilize.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.30,0:46:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing you know, he's going to take over 16 more casinos in South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.40,0:46:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.71,0:46:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.78,0:46:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.03,0:46:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.63,0:46:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.42,0:46:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.21,0:46:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.92,0:46:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's become a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.92,0:46:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a game he enjoys.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.98,0:46:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, he's good at bridge, and he wins at bridge, and you're good at poker, you're good at shooting craps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.00,0:46:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He enjoys the game of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.67,0:46:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.23,0:47:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at Donald, you'll see how much he enjoys the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.28,0:47:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He really just loves the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.09,0:47:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to take over all the gambling in South America and build new casinos across the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.94,0:47:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.98,0:47:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He does it because he likes to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.34,0:47:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets the fun of it, the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.84,0:47:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So he just loves doing what he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.40,0:47:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what makes him run.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.57,0:47:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, not greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.61,0:47:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got enough money already.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.73,0:47:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't possibly spend it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.17,0:47:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.61,0:47:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fun of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.00,0:47:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's the fun of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.00,0:47:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Like being good at poker, it's the fun of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.67,0:47:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Capitalize on these frenetic energy surges, and in between them, just plow the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.09,0:47:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.17,0:47:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's times when you're just bursting with all kinds of brilliant energy and genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.17,0:47:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,strokes of genius, and you write these all down on the notepad next to your bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.76,0:47:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then until that happens again, you plow it along, plow it along.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.50,0:48:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,101 ways to success.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.84,0:48:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So 55 of them were inspirational.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.46,0:48:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,10 of them were goofy ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.09,0:48:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest of them are just plowing along.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.48,0:48:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.11,0:48:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, obviously, you expect success.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.17,0:48:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have an inner integrity begin to expect success.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.21,0:48:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that if you put your mind to a project, it's going to turn out all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.03,0:48:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that if you're going to make a jug of iced tea for this afternoon, you know that it's going to be good iced tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.75,0:48:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can learn to depend on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.92,0:48:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, kneel down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.71,0:48:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.25,0:48:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.44,0:48:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.51,0:48:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Media capacity means it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.34,0:48:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to get a little niche of the world that's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.23,0:48:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Donald sort of has that niche.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.23,0:49:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Donald Trump has that niche in gambling casinos and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.40,0:49:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have not done anything much in gambling casinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.21,0:49:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I figure that belongs to Donald.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.09,0:49:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He sends me notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.90,0:49:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Dave, for leaving gambling casinos international to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.40,0:49:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He moves across the...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.78,0:49:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,globe south america then he moved to egypt and asia uh nailed down especially right about your
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.78,0:49:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,project is a way of organizing yourself and it'll bring in thoughts that you didn't have until you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.28,0:49:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,actually wrote it down do a sale do these are practice steps here do a sales pitch on video
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.96,0:49:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,now that activates a whole lot of energies that you weren't aware of for
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.11,0:49:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,see because we're visual auditory cerebral and so these different modalities when you do a sales
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.92,0:50:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,pitch you're doing it in movement you're doing it in speech you're doing it as a style of presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.94,0:50:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you do a video on some project your understanding of the project will be different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.90,0:50:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the video than at the start of the video so if you have a thing that can make videos
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.40,0:50:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at home
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.44,0:50:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you try that whether it's designing a new dress or how are you going to fix up your car whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.44,0:50:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to do give yourself a sales pitch on video now dave i think if you uh this next
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.63,0:50:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture if you talk about success if i were you i wouldn't besides the following points
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.84,0:50:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't and you know so i remind myself i don't want to forget donald trump let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.17,0:50:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,uh do a sales pitch on video you want to promise yourself periodic rewards that at a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.55,0:50:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,period of time you're going to acknowledge your own creativity and take pleasure in it and share it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.07,0:51:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with your family or share it with with your wife and i like to share my stuff with my wife and then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.63,0:51:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,both of us can comment on it and then that starts to hold further development of the thought process
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.40,0:51:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,aside from doing a videos you can do photo photos of yourself in a successful role this is a good
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.53,0:51:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,way of uh image imaging to your audience and i think that's a good way to do that so i'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.80,0:51:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a little bit more about what you want to do with yourself what you want to really reflect to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.98,0:51:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the world and uh so if you take some photographs of yourself and you look you begin to notice
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.84,0:51:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you know actually you look like a slob everything's unbuttoned your hair is a mess i mean
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.76,0:51:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so you begin to be aware that that which you are also expresses itself non-verbally
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.63,0:51:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not only in style and language and gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.05,0:51:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way you dress in your manner and the manner in which you carry yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.92,0:52:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so making photos of yourself in a successful role
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.51,0:52:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of affirming that aspect that of your life that you're trying to grow into
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.71,0:52:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,take a picture of yourself and on your desk you put president i mean you've got a company
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.61,0:52:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,going and company you're working for so you just put the science as president you take
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.30,0:52:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a picture of yourself as president you know that creates an image in your head
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.76,0:52:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you your your your consciousness will be drawn to that image now you never really thought
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.82,0:52:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about being president of this company before but the minute you do that you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.26,0:52:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah you could be actually and all of a sudden you see the pathway becoming president this guy's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.88,0:52:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,going to retire this guy isn't worth a crap anyway this guy about sold this one i can tell
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.15,0:52:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of lies about and they'll believe me anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.59,0:52:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to become that which you think you are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.01,0:53:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of politicians do that they see themselves as senator from something or other and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.26,0:53:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,congressman from something or other they see them as you know some kind of a big hoop to do
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.48,0:53:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,now the big time hoopty do uh news commentaries on television uh actually form the people that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.96,0:53:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they're supposed to represent see you begin to become that which you think you are a lot of politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.61,0:53:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,become your role so the five o'clock news reports that you have gone to congress
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.55,0:53:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,buy new cadillacs for all the poor people in south america and uh the next thing you know you're buying
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.03,0:53:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,new cadillacs for all the people in south america and you voted into office as the cadillac president
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.19,0:53:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you've just created that role manifested it in an audio visual manner so audio visual
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.15,0:54:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite powerful much of what is happening in today's world is not the cause of the nightly news
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.40,0:54:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the consequence of it did you ever think of that it's the nightly news that's causing tomorrow's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.82,0:54:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,news yeah you think you're reporting today's news no you're creating today's news by what
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.26,0:54:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,attention and energy you give to what subjects the attention and energy you give to certain
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.26,0:54:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,subjects then creates the reality of the nightly news and you're creating the nightly news and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.50,0:54:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the audio-visual image of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.09,0:54:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the TV news is quite powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.55,0:54:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason I track it is because it tells me
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.21,0:54:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what's happening in various areas of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.09,0:54:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which may or may not have surfaced yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.86,0:54:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know that they're going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.36,0:54:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.55,0:54:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Give yourself a dollar for each great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.26,0:54:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.55,0:54:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to give people a dollar for all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.36,0:54:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When they'd come up, they'd give me a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.07,0:55:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that up in Peru.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.86,0:55:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Peru up in the Andes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.75,0:55:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many feet it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.40,0:55:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 feet, 8,000 feet, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.15,0:55:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm up in Peru there near Machu Picchu
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.28,0:55:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,all by myself, I think, in the middle of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.09,0:55:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was this little girl sitting there with a llama.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.23,0:55:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And a little girl about this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.82,0:55:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's holding this llama.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.51,0:55:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had a camera, so I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.30,0:55:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, my gosh, it was a beautiful scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.90,0:55:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are the Andes Mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.17,0:55:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.07,0:55:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This beautiful setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.32,0:55:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this country girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.98,0:55:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's this llama.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.11,0:55:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's holding the llama's harness by the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.63,0:55:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had this camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.21,0:55:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to her, do you mind if I take your picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.98,0:55:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, that'll be a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.94,0:55:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.67,0:55:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where I got the phrase,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.28,0:55:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that'll be a dollar from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.09,0:55:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I use it in many a thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.07,0:56:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.40,0:56:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,People used to ask a question after a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.34,0:56:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, that'll be a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.34,0:56:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So pretty soon, I had a bunch of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.38,0:56:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, it came spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.19,0:56:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,from this beautiful little girl high up in the Andes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.28,0:56:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.05,0:56:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.59,0:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Give yourself a dollar for each great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.59,0:56:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you'll see as time goes on, they pile up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.28,0:56:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To thine own self be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.26,0:56:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To thine own self be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.48,0:56:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is to the integrity, the reality of that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.63,0:56:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.71,0:56:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit of a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.94,0:56:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit of a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.21,0:56:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit of a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.38,0:56:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To be true to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.73,0:56:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If your innate nature is to be kind towards and forgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.42,0:56:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then be true to that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.07,0:56:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the crowd is roaring for the guillotine,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.17,0:56:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not in the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.59,0:56:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's not your way of seeing the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.90,0:56:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The way I see the world, people make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.21,0:56:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't behead them for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.11,0:56:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in beheading them for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.01,0:57:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the days of the guillotine,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.15,0:57:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess there was quite a mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.65,0:57:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And 14,000 people got guillotined.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.25,0:57:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After the French Revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.76,0:57:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was 15,000 people were guillotined.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.76,0:57:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some people were in the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.40,0:57:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoyed watching the guillotine come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.71,0:57:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people avoided it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.73,0:57:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to thine own self be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.59,0:57:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Put together an inspirational collage.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.65,0:57:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that's a big thing you can hang on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.00,0:57:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you put various things in that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.36,0:57:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're trained to bring about,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.13,0:57:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a phenomenon in the world using a variety of techniques,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.88,0:57:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.94,0:57:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconscious suggestion, imaging, role playing, pictorial,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.03,0:57:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a collage of all the things you would have if you were that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.57,0:57:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, if you want to be successful and have a Cadillac,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.71,0:57:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you get pictures of Cadillacs and you put them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.28,0:57:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I've got pictures of jet planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.84,0:58:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no ambition to buy a jet plane,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.11,0:58:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but they just inspire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.53,0:58:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the incredible beauty of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.42,0:58:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nothing more sleek looking than a jet plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.17,0:58:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it is probably the sleekest looking thing on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.09,0:58:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just got this long nose and it just takes off like a wild animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.32,0:58:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just breathtaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.17,0:58:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, right now, I'm in love with jet planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.01,0:58:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the big ones that the multimillionaires have.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.57,0:58:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are like big buses.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.42,0:58:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, these are the little ones that take half a dozen people, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.88,0:58:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Little jet planes are just, to me, a turn on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.65,0:58:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I love little jet planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.26,0:58:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I was super rich, I'd buy a little jet plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.15,0:58:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And any time I wanted to go someplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.71,0:58:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd run out and jump in my jet plane and take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.71,0:58:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's 50 miles, I can take a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.23,0:58:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fun of taking off and then landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.80,0:59:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, even if you only went 50 miles, I'd go everywhere by jet plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.30,0:59:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.69,0:59:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.21,0:59:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Give yourself a dollar for your jet plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.26,0:59:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Give yourself a dollar for each great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.86,0:59:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, be true to yourself, your own standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.48,0:59:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Put together an inspirational collage, a collection of things that image what you are holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.61,0:59:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I keep putting pictures of jet planes up on my bulletin board,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.69,0:59:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere out of the blue one might emerge, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.92,0:59:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.98,0:59:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Be on the road of enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.53,0:59:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that means that you should be traveling in the direction
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.98,0:59:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have in mind for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.50,0:59:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultivating the relationships that would be supportive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.30,0:59:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultivating the intellectual input.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.21,0:59:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The learning, the courses you could be taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.42,0:59:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to be a genius to build a better mouse trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.57,0:59:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.90,1:00:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that this is a consequence of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.50,1:00:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what the world needs, and you just sort of automatically try to invent something that will,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.73,1:00:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.94,1:00:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, over the years, I've invented a number of things just for my own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.57,1:00:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, any one of them could become a product that you could then
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.13,1:00:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,advertise and sell and manufacture.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.01,1:00:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarity of your goals.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.76,1:00:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By success, what are the exact goals?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.92,1:00:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by success?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.76,1:00:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarify the goals means to nail down in a concrete fashion exactly what you mean by success.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.36,1:00:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Move on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.44,1:00:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Move on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.63,1:00:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, any of you that are interested in success, it's important to get a page and write down
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.19,1:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what you mean by a success in all the details.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.38,1:01:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean driving a Cadillac or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.73,1:01:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean taking a cab and not having to bother with owning a car?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.09,1:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean having servants?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.46,1:01:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean having a great big house?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.98,1:01:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean having security and coziness?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.13,1:01:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I like cozy security.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.90,1:01:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I like a little cozy place off in the woods someplace, and nobody knows I'm there except
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.50,1:01:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the birds and the animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.26,1:01:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to me, success is cozy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.73,1:01:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Cozy and nature, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.82,1:01:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not other people's idea, but I like country simplicity in the middle of the woods
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.61,1:01:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.09,1:01:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, I like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.21,1:01:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear the birds and the animals galloping around, and that's it, instead of the sound
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.80,1:01:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of city traffic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.76,1:01:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people like the sound of city traffic, and when traffic comes to a halt, they feel
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.84,1:01:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.40,1:01:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.86,1:01:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I had somebody that would come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.15,1:02:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She lived in New York City, and she would come out to the country and spend the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.73,1:02:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The country was quiet and still, and as the weekend went on, she got more and more depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.21,1:02:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.09,1:02:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.05,1:02:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't wait to get back to the city with the sound of garbage cans clanking at 3 in the morning
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.26,1:02:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and traffic going by and horns and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.53,1:02:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So she was back in the city, and she was happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.94,1:02:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But being out in the quiet, beautiful countryside made her very depressed and felt lonely.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.28,1:02:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's city people and there's country people.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.69,1:02:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to decide, am I a city person or a country person?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.30,1:02:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, put your heart instead of the ego into the project.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.75,1:02:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means passion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.55,1:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart is passion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.59,1:02:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you put your passion into the project instead of just the ego's idea of gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.94,1:02:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego sees success in terms of gain, titles and money and positions, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.23,1:03:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart sees it as fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.44,1:03:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you put your heart into the project instead of your ego, you'll find that it takes less energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.23,1:03:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To fulfill it for the ego's ends takes energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.40,1:03:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.26,1:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes energy to propel it for ego gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.96,1:03:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're doing it out of the passion, out of the love for the project, that doesn't take any energy out of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.88,1:03:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, by the time you finish the project, you'll feel more energetic than you did before you started it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.78,1:03:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used to make, when I was into archery, I was into archery for years,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.25,1:03:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I would make my own bows and arrows and make my own bows and arrows.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.75,1:03:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was just passion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.15,1:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just greater gratification in archery with a bow that I had made myself and with arrows that were absolutely perfect that I myself had put together.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.07,1:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So put your heart instead of just the ego into the project.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.17,1:04:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So your heart means your love for it, your love for it, your passion for it, instead of the gain from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.17,1:04:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what gain did I ever get out of being good at archery?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.86,1:04:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.26,1:04:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a couple of archery medals, if I remember rightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.28,1:04:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But once you got a couple of archery medals, a few more don't any good.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.71,1:04:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do it for the love of the sport, not just because you have to be a winner.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.84,1:04:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people in sports understand this very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.84,1:04:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The love of the sport is what puts them out on the practice ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.50,1:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll do for love of the sport that which they would never do for money.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.63,1:04:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Which aspects of your project are ego and which are soul?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.05,1:04:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego and the soul is just a different way of expressing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.28,1:04:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is looking for gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we mentioned before, not only just gain, but the glamour of the gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.80,1:05:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the book I mentioned, did I mention the glamour this morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.61,1:05:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.01,1:05:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.73,1:05:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.51,1:05:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've mentioned Alice Bailey's book on glamour before in other lectures, many other lectures, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.80,1:05:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey was a sportsman.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.96,1:05:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey was a sportsman.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.05,1:05:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey was a sportsman.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.07,1:05:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And she wrote a book called, called what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.00,1:05:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.78,1:05:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.46,1:05:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.00,1:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The book is called Glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.57,1:05:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.73,1:05:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.51,1:05:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, glamour is not an imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.21,1:05:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.57,1:05:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an actual energy that you can calibrate and measure.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.42,1:05:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's called glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.28,1:05:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And glamour is what you project onto something out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.48,1:05:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You think what's attractive is that Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.00,1:05:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.61,1:05:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the glamour that you project onto the Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.48,1:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's more, it's greater than life size.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.15,1:06:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a car anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.19,1:06:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a royal chariot.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.90,1:06:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.53,1:06:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.48,1:06:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a Cadillac owner.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.61,1:06:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had this Cadillac since I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.03,1:06:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought it used in 1984 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.78,1:06:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What year is that Cadillac?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.34,1:06:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,84?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.96,1:06:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's 84.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.65,1:06:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,84, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.42,1:06:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's an 84 Cadillac and I bought it in 89 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.78,1:06:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this Cadillac still sits up in my property and it's carefully polished and we repainted it and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.28,1:06:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I never take it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.15,1:06:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that it is mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.28,1:06:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I used to take it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.94,1:06:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd take it to town.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.65,1:06:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was the only old Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.86,1:06:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Shiny old Cadillac in town.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.19,1:07:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody's head would turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.48,1:07:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd look at this big old Cadillac going by.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.42,1:07:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.98,1:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, it's what it stood for.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.98,1:07:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of that old Caddy was just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.17,1:07:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah, that's putting your heart instead of your ego into the project because money-wise it's not worth all that much.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.07,1:07:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Which aspects of your project are ego and which ones are the essence of that which you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.13,1:07:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is success just a feeling or is it a reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.19,1:07:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is success something real or is it something you would just project onto it?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.96,1:07:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You say getting to a certain level, you know, in your eyes makes you a success.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.11,1:07:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that just a feeling or is that a reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.44,1:07:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Would other people agree with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.53,1:07:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And would it make any difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.15,1:07:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There are times when it doesn't make any difference whether other people consider you a success or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.11,1:08:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether other people admire my old Caddy or not is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.90,1:08:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.11,1:08:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a feeling rather than a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.32,1:08:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-rewarding versus public adulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.51,1:08:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is success self-rewarding or are you looking for the hurrah of the crowd?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.23,1:08:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-rewarding versus public adulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.81,1:08:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.56,1:08:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's self-rewarding, then you're independent of the public's reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.61,1:08:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you're wanting public adulation, the public applause,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.02,1:08:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you're now the victim of the media and everything out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.93,1:08:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If your self-rewarding means you want to be the best congressman you can
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.31,1:08:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've taken a vow to do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.57,1:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,people who take these things, they put their hand on the Bible, they swear by things and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.77,1:09:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see how they can avoid the obligations that they take upon themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.42,1:09:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-rewarding means that you have fulfilled your understanding rather than pleasing the public.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.63,1:09:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I'm going to be a good congressman, I've got to satisfy my own conscience,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.97,1:09:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,not necessarily please the public.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.85,1:09:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're answerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.19,1:09:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A person of integrity is answerable to themself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.84,1:09:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Answerable to themself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.11,1:09:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A person of less integrity is only interested in the adulation of the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.09,1:09:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The cheer of the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.85,1:09:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're aware that that is your purpose and that is your goal and that's acceptable to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.51,1:09:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing wrong with it, but at least you're not fooling yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.64,1:09:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you're doing this, that, and the other thing is you want to get re-elected,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.09,1:09:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,not because you believe in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.94,1:09:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear a politician, he gets home and says to his wife,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.22,1:09:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,man, what a bunch of horseshit I did today, but I won the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.55,1:10:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He won the vote, even though it's complete and total BS.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.64,1:10:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-rewarding versus public adulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.18,1:10:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is adequate to your lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.65,1:10:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Adequate to your lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.84,1:10:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means success has to be appropriate to that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.89,1:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people pretend greater success than they have.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.60,1:10:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people are sort of chronically poor-looking,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.31,1:10:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,even though their mattress is stuffed with money, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.69,1:10:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, number 80, to be light-hearted versus being grim.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.46,1:10:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That the pathway to success should be pleasant and easygoing instead of white-knuckled.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.09,1:10:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see many people trying for success and it's sort of pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.64,1:10:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your heart goes out for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.05,1:11:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To such extremes they go for that which should be automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.84,1:11:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because success...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.65,1:11:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is really being adequate rather than being some kind of an olympic star.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.81,1:11:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And to be adequate means to utilize the faculties that you have just normally,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.39,1:11:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but use them with a goal in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.98,1:11:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When one way to success is merely being friendly and pleasant and good partnership.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.64,1:11:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think of somebody you want to accompany you on the road to success,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.06,1:11:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want somebody who's white-knuckled, boring, and grim.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.68,1:11:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so success is really a general, more general kind of an attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.18,1:11:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of being dependable and reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.56,1:12:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Being pleasant, agreeable, friendly, dependable, and reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.97,1:12:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Success as being responsible as well as reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.94,1:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you're willing to be accountable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.97,1:12:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're willing to be responsible for your efforts and therefore it's important
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.47,1:12:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop giving energy to self-doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.97,1:12:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why give energy to that which is negative?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.57,1:12:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire is to produce the best possible performance whether you're on a job or you're
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.31,1:12:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on a trip, you're doing a minor repair on the car, whatever it is, there's a pleasure
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.56,1:12:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in knowing that you've done the best possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.64,1:12:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done the best possible job you could at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.97,1:12:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't compare it to the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.39,1:12:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you'd had, you know, $100 worth of equipment, you could have done a better job.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.18,1:13:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the car breaks down, you get it going again, you know, the normal person is being, is pleased.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.35,1:13:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's just a normalcy to success.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.01,1:13:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch the whole animal kingdom and they're happy when they have achieved something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.03,1:13:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My dog is happy as a clam when she goes to Pippin.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.11,1:13:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes to pick up something she's lost and finds it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.68,1:13:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's just a normal mammalian kind of a pleasure in being alive and functioning
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.52,1:13:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in a successful, self-rewarding way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.76,1:13:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the excuse of trying and make a decision to do a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.72,1:13:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So trying was never an excuse that was allowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.11,1:13:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't supposed to try to mix things with your tinker toy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.89,1:13:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You were supposed to make them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.53,1:13:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Make an engine.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.14,1:13:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a locomotive with that and not try to make a locomotive with it, but make a locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.73,1:13:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.73,1:13:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.73,1:13:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You got from that to do it, not to fake it, but to actually do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.13,1:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was sort of a commonly known phrase a couple of decades ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.32,1:14:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the excuse of trying and just do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.64,1:14:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to do a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.97,1:14:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.97,1:14:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand the difference of trying to do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.35,1:14:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to do it puts it in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.15,1:14:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing it puts it in the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.36,1:14:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to get, you know, somewhere, rather.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.89,1:14:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to get somewhere on this book, the only way to do that is to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.97,1:14:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.28,1:14:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't publish trying.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.89,1:14:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only publish what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.78,1:14:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.78,1:14:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Another trick is write down all the negatives and bury them in the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.27,1:14:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, a lot of these things you say, you know, the adult in you says, oh, that's so
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.55,1:14:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,childish.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.47,1:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So forget the adult in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.93,1:14:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And listen to the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.93,1:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.68,1:14:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The child says, we're going to dig a hole in the background and we're going to go and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.01,1:14:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,put it all in there and bury it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.26,1:15:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I remember as a boy in camp, we used to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.07,1:15:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd dig a big hole in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.96,1:15:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you had any resentments against your fellow campers, we would all sit around the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.89,1:15:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,campfire and there'd be this hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.56,1:15:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'd all have to take our resentments against some other kid and put them in this
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.64,1:15:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.76,1:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we were all done putting our resentments in this hole, we covered it up with dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.15,1:15:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, that's silly.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.68,1:15:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not silly because you're actualizing something that would otherwise be in the abstract,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.15,1:15:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,non-specific.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.30,1:15:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So acting out, acting out then symbolically.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.14,1:15:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We typically do this in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.25,1:15:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We typically act out by various means.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.94,1:15:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.94,1:15:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.94,1:15:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.94,1:15:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.94,1:15:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.94,1:15:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in religious life.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.94,1:15:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.94,1:15:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.94,1:15:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.94,1:15:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.94,1:15:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.97,1:15:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.97,1:16:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that which is symbolized by the body's motions, et cetera, it brings
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.14,1:16:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it to a different level.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.14,1:16:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say, to thee, oh, Lord, most high, that's different than saying, to thee, oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.98,1:16:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord, most high.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.98,1:16:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go to culture in India, or you go to South Vietnam, no, where do we go?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.31,1:16:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to Korea?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.02,1:16:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.02,1:16:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.02,1:16:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where that's part of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.02,1:16:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's part of our culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.02,1:16:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the gentility of the civilization is built in, that each one, I bow to the God within
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.92,1:16:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,me, that you acknowledge the divinity of each entity, and there is a profound strength in
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.46,1:16:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.10,1:16:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a communication of spiritual reality that does not exist other than through the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.92,1:16:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,physical, through the physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.43,1:16:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, identify helpful contacts.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.35,1:16:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're talking, but we're back again to the practical, the value of having feedback
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.02,1:17:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from consultants and experts.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.60,1:17:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Identify helpful contacts.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.72,1:17:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would be helpful to you in developing your idea and moving it forward?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.27,1:17:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one, some may only add a few ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.02,1:17:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if I were you, I'd make it blue instead of green.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.47,1:17:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll show up better.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.43,1:17:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.10,1:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so do the brain gym.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.90,1:17:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain gym exercise of the road to be traveled.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.09,1:17:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what brain gym is?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.82,1:17:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain gym is you put your neurons through the whole exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.77,1:17:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You picture yourself sitting down.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.78,1:17:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You picture yourself picking up the pen.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.35,1:17:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You picture yourself writing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.63,1:17:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You picture yourself proofreading it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.64,1:17:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You picture yourself getting a type.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.55,1:17:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're going to read the typed copy, and you're going to correct the typed copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.43,1:17:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you picture yourself dictating the corrections and then communicating the corrections, and
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.39,1:17:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then you picture yourself, you know, correcting the corrections.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.97,1:17:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get a good copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.56,1:18:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the brain gym goes through all of the things that you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.35,1:18:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow the neurons and the dendrites, the dendrites connect with each other depending
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.72,1:18:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on how you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.42,1:18:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you picture something happening, these little dendrites loop over and connect with
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.52,1:18:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this dendrite.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.52,1:18:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you picture the continuation of that movement, and that little dendrite, as it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.52,1:18:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,grows, it flops around like this, and it connects with this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.64,1:18:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see pretty soon you've connected up a whole circuitry in your brain in the dendritic
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.03,1:18:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,processes, because these dendrites are constantly forming and collapsing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.57,1:18:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So as these dendrites are waving around, they're saying, where shall I go?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.92,1:18:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where shall I go?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.92,1:18:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, go here, oh, genius, oh, okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.14,1:18:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this dendrite begins to wave around and says, where shall I go?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.92,1:18:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, well, come over here and draw the face of a doggie, oh, now it's a doggie
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.73,1:18:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,face.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.73,1:19:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now draw a kitty sitting on the back of the doggie, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.80,1:19:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So pretty soon the picture begins to develop and emerge of its own as the dendrites are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.38,1:19:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,waving around.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.38,1:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way to stay young and flexible is to realize that your dendrites are constantly
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.31,1:19:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,waving around in your brain no matter how old you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.77,1:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wave as much maybe when you get older, but I hear them waving, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.76,1:19:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear them waving, oh, gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.57,1:19:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, take advantage of the fact that these dendrites are constantly forming synapses,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.13,1:19:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a synapse is a connection, so they're available.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.93,1:19:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So these dendrites are asking you all the time, what should I pay attention to?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.82,1:19:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.89,1:19:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you picture yourself writing a book and then sit down and begin to write the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.22,1:20:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the dendrites say, oh, he's writing a book, oh, she wants to write a book on cooking.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.60,1:20:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.60,1:20:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So now the little dendrites begin to form a pattern and they merge with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.47,1:20:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of just flopping around loose like that, they begin to make synapses.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.96,1:20:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the brain now begins to, the brain gym means that your neurons, the dendrites, are
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.69,1:20:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,gonna connect up with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.23,1:20:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way form...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.88,1:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a functional unit in your brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.14,1:20:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the brain gym exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.14,1:20:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It pictures you going out on the ball field,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.06,1:20:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,wiping off the bat, pulling up your socks,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.77,1:20:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,lining yourself, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.47,1:20:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It does everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.84,1:20:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you energize each step, each step.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.46,1:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So not just the overall pattern, but each step of the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.07,1:20:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when I remember that ditch that I dug,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.40,1:20:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I would get ferocious with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.02,1:20:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, here's this big log, quarter of a mile long or whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.67,1:21:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and its earth had not been moved before,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.28,1:21:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's virgin earth, and I'm getting there, pushing down,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.75,1:21:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and there I said, I'm going to do six feet today, six feet, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.09,1:21:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I get to six feet, and all of a sudden my mind would look ahead,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.25,1:21:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would see another six feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.93,1:21:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just would look ahead and see that six feet,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.07,1:21:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd say, ah, the hell with it, and I'd go after that six feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.50,1:21:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing you know, I had 12 feet, and I had to stop myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.18,1:21:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'd be going on to 18 feet, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.25,1:21:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which you energize develops a certain momentum of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.17,1:21:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Highly successful people learn how to take advantage of momentum,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.52,1:21:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,how to energize, how to move those dendrites to be connected correctly,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.39,1:21:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how to get yourself enthused.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.06,1:21:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact you've got enough gambling casinos already is not what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.90,1:21:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the game of building gambling casinos.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.64,1:21:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So with yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.09,1:21:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and your brain gym,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.68,1:22:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a game of working towards fulfilling an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.35,1:22:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I get the inspiration about a certain kind of book,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.18,1:22:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,here's what I want to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.90,1:22:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to say it yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.40,1:22:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm already thinking about it in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.68,1:22:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have a book I have in mind that I want to write.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.01,1:22:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of little short things that I've noticed in life
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.94,1:22:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can't make a whole book out of,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.40,1:22:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're significant,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.18,1:22:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and things people...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.06,1:22:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't recognize.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.81,1:22:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, I'd like to write a book on essays.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.81,1:22:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Essays.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.90,1:22:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Things you've noticed, especially in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.89,1:22:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The way things are phrased,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.71,1:22:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the trickeries that are put on that people seem to be unconscious of.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.59,1:22:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of things that would be fun to comment on.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.78,1:22:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figure when you're old enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.39,1:22:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you can just publish your, you know, essays and commentaries,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.27,1:22:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and if people don't like them, the hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.22,1:23:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least you've had your say, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.10,1:23:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should have their say before they go.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.06,1:23:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you haven't got a book on essays yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.19,1:23:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you should start a book on essays.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.47,1:23:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your commentaries on life,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.35,1:23:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it reflects your values,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.39,1:23:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and many observations that other people don't make.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.43,1:23:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite is television advertising.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.02,1:23:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I could write a whole book on television advertising,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.27,1:23:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and that advertisers would benefit from.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.13,1:23:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There are ads out there that cost a zillion dollars,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.42,1:23:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're incredible turn-offs.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.38,1:23:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I use the arm and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.10,1:23:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this ad is an incredible turn-off, she goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.10,1:23:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates an aversion to their products.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.46,1:23:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The people, the companies are spending millions of dollars on ads
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.46,1:23:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that create an aversion to their product.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.46,1:23:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to yourself, if they run that ad one more time,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.61,1:23:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.34,1:24:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you just been drummed to death by some stupid ad?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.63,1:24:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a guy whose head comes out of the ceiling upside down,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.72,1:24:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and his head is next to somebody whose head is outside up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.51,1:24:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's holding his head like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.72,1:24:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the dumbest thing I ever saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.13,1:24:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is it's supposed to be selling, I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.86,1:24:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so stupid, I'm just there in stupid shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.14,1:24:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's supposed to be selling something.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.38,1:24:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.43,1:24:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This disturbed teenagers write these ads, or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.50,1:24:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who writes them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.14,1:24:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For sheer stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.19,1:24:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they repeat it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.19,1:24:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was dumb the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.93,1:24:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was stupid the second time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.69,1:24:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was idiotic the third time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.59,1:24:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate their product.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.05,1:24:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I am never going to buy their crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.82,1:24:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.26,1:24:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially the 140th time I've seen that dumb ad.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.21,1:24:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,140 times on the same stupid ad.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.71,1:24:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hated it in the beginning, and now I loathe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.25,1:25:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Loathe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.81,1:25:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I go all the way around to avoid their product.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.11,1:25:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's super stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.81,1:25:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't buy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.81,1:25:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the last thing they had for sale in the grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.86,1:25:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that these advertising companies are creating an aversion for their product
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.01,1:25:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,never dawned on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.77,1:25:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody ever hear of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.73,1:25:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.73,1:25:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.73,1:25:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're spending millions of dollars to create an aversion to their product.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.22,1:25:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,People hate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.22,1:25:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.44,1:25:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.06,1:25:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear the name of that product one more time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.82,1:25:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If that idiot with his head coming out of the ceiling upside down wants to sell me anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.48,1:25:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't buy it if he gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.42,1:25:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, don't get me started on TV advertising because I can go for a half an hour on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.85,1:26:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just getting steamed up on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.28,1:26:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Energize.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.28,1:26:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid ethically dubious schemes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.28,1:26:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, if there's anything that makes you tiddly about a thing, it's best to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.50,1:26:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid ethically dubious schemes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.50,1:26:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder about some politicians because there's nothing that seems ethically
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.89,1:26:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,dubious to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.89,1:26:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We've used the arm on some of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.68,1:26:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's scary.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.68,1:26:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid ethically dubious schemes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.68,1:26:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you one reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.68,1:26:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the person you are now at this age, it may be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.68,1:26:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a little okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.68,1:26:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Shady.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.68,1:26:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you get older, your ethical responsibilities seem to be more demanding and heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.85,1:26:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So a chancy, dubious, morally dubious scheme that you pulled off at 25, at 45, it's going
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.85,1:26:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.85,1:27:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.85,1:27:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At 45, you're going to say, Jesus, why did I do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.85,1:27:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I must have really been stooped.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.85,1:27:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At 65, it's really a burden.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.85,1:27:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 85, you know you're going to meet God pretty soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.10,1:27:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got this black spot on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.47,1:27:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you when I was a kid, sin was explained to me as a spot on your soul that God could
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.93,1:27:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,see.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.93,1:27:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy smokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.93,1:27:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, that's a heavy trip for a kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.42,1:27:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got this invisible screen behind you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.42,1:27:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And any kind of a sin shows up as a black spot on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.48,1:27:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy smokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.48,1:27:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's God up there looking down on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.48,1:27:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's this screen behind you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.48,1:27:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And sins are showing up as smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.48,1:27:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sins are showing up as smudges on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.48,1:27:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Soul smudges.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.89,1:27:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.89,1:27:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin smudges.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.89,1:27:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.51,1:27:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I went to confession every Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.51,1:28:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Went to confession every Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.68,1:28:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.35,1:28:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he'd give you absolution, but I wasn't sure if it was really complete absolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.35,1:28:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It might have been almost complete absolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.98,1:28:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The black was wiped out, but there might be some gray in my soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.38,1:28:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God would look down and see this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.38,1:28:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wiggly gray shade.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.38,1:28:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you about it after going to the confession.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.07,1:28:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to communion once in the morning on the way to church.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.21,1:28:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this 30-foot billboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.23,1:28:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And here was the Jansen swimsuit ad.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.23,1:28:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is back in the 30s.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.81,1:28:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a one-piece suit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.61,1:28:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Very discreet by today's Sanders.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.61,1:28:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But here's this 100-foot long blonde.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.61,1:28:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm driving by this 100-foot blonde.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.38,1:28:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In a swimsuit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.38,1:29:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the top's down on the old convertible.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.38,1:29:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm trying not to have any sinful thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.38,1:29:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She's 30 feet long and curvaceous.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.78,1:29:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was an old-fashioned one-piece swimming suit.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.43,1:29:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By today's standards, you know, it would be nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.43,1:29:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You could wear it on the street and nobody would even notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.43,1:29:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But in that era, back in the 50s or whenever it was, before that, 30s maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.26,1:29:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I was afraid it might have energized a sinful thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.26,1:29:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.68,1:29:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your heart instead of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.68,1:29:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.71,1:29:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And to differentiate which is ego and which is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.73,1:29:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the excuse of trying and just do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.73,1:29:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Write down all the negatives and put them in the backyard, we said.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.02,1:29:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Have supportive relationships.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.13,1:29:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Fake it till you make it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.13,1:29:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Select a role model.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.13,1:29:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide to be happy no matter what the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.35,1:29:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.35,1:29:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.35,1:30:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Be happy through the effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.47,1:30:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, by your commitment to express the best of that which you are capable.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.18,1:30:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To be helpful to society in all of its ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.18,1:30:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The image I have of the perfect life is to be that which lights up the world wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.89,1:30:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is integrous and aligned with the will of God lights up the woods.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.88,1:30:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you walk through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.88,1:30:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,every tree knows that you're passing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.10,1:30:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is lit up by the love of God and acknowledges God as the creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.35,1:30:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When they walk through the woods...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.35,1:30:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When they walk through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.28,1:30:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole woods knows it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.28,1:30:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.42,1:30:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for interrupting your...interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.10,1:31:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things are supposed to go on behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.10,1:31:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.10,1:31:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.10,1:31:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, I was very shy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.10,1:31:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so as a kindergartner, I was in this...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.10,1:31:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to be behind this Christmas tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.10,1:31:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Big cardboard Christmas tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.10,1:31:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the key word, I was supposed to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.10,1:31:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Robin, hop, hop, hop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.10,1:31:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was supposed to hop, hop, hop in front of this tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.10,1:31:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then back around behind the tree again.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.10,1:31:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So the teacher says,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.17,1:31:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Robin, hop, hop, hop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.17,1:31:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wouldn't come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.17,1:31:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd stay behind the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.17,1:31:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Robin, hop, hop, hop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.17,1:31:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd say it louder and louder.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.17,1:31:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wouldn't come out from behind the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.34,1:31:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Robin, hop, hop, hop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.34,1:31:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were just doing a Robin, hop, hop, hop on the side.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.32,1:31:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision to be happy no matter what the result
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.32,1:32:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,means that the source of your happiness is not consequent upon the world or performance.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.32,1:32:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is a style.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.03,1:32:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.03,1:32:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And this way of being guarantees the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.06,1:32:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This way of being guarantees that all outcomes will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.84,1:32:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That all of them will be acceptable and positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.18,1:32:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's okay to be a shy Robin and not come out from behind the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.85,1:32:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.85,1:32:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, Why didn't you come out from behind the tree?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.85,1:32:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm shy.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.89,1:32:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.85,1:32:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,End of story.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.85,1:32:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm too shy to be a Robin in kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.85,1:32:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had to be reborn, I wouldn't go to kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.06,1:33:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to get you into some rotten kindergarten play.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.06,1:33:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all to pull out the parents and the aunts and the grandparents to go and see little Joey and be a Robin in a play.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.57,1:33:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for the parents and the grandparents and the aunts and the uncles.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.57,1:33:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to go and see them and be a Robin in the kindergarten play.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.10,1:33:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you have been to a kindergarten play?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.10,1:33:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.10,1:33:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever survive it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.10,1:33:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.10,1:33:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because you love little tots and they're all cute, you go and it is sort of a fun exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.10,1:33:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a fun exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.10,1:33:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.28,1:33:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have supportive relationships about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.28,1:33:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And there should be coaches on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.28,1:33:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Select a role model.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.73,1:33:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide to be happy no matter what the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.73,1:33:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a happy person means that you live according to certain rules and guidelines and qualifications.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.96,1:34:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you don't have to have a result.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.96,1:34:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You just have to be that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.96,1:34:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that you're as friendly as you can be and as helpful as you can be doesn't mean that you have to be popular.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.96,1:34:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're just doing that to be popular,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.96,1:34:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that's quite a different thing than just doing that because that's the kind of a person you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.96,1:34:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're that kind of a person.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.11,1:34:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that great success is often fortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.50,1:34:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Great success is often fortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.56,1:34:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, some of the greatest success stories in the world, many of them or a lot of them, one list I once made, all of them were fortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.72,1:34:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You just happen to notice something at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.72,1:34:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You just happen to notice something at the right time and in the right motion.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.72,1:34:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, we give the discovery that eventually led to the development of penicillin to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.72,1:35:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when you notice the petri dish or the dust blew in, the mold didn't grow there.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.72,1:35:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And discovering why, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.81,1:35:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the basic discovery that led eventually to the discovery of penicillin
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.30,1:35:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and changed the history of World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.30,1:35:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So people who used to die from infections now got a shot of penicillin.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.30,1:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And one million units of penicillin will cure just about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.34,1:35:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was fortuitous, fortuitous, fortuitous observations.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.34,1:35:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the world's, many of the world's greatest discoveries were just fortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.34,1:35:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.34,1:35:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The person, the witness became enhanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.34,1:35:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Enhanced by the observation that is, you know, the fact that truth makes you go strong
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.68,1:35:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood makes you go weak is really fortuitous, fortuitous, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.72,1:36:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither one of us ever think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.97,1:36:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's so automatic and it's so almost infallible that we've incorporated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.26,1:36:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's fortuitous but extremely useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.38,1:36:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't create any product in the world, much less profit,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.38,1:36:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but it does show people.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.43,1:36:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? I've got five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.01,1:36:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she's a rough coach.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.01,1:36:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, such a mean disciplinarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.46,1:36:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have 97 to go to.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.84,1:36:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have what? Just this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.84,1:36:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This one last sheet thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.89,1:36:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.89,1:36:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay attention to the facts of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.31,1:36:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Running out of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.93,1:36:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If time doesn't give a rap about us, why should I give a rap about time?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.22,1:36:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.22,1:37:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, we're all very self-infortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.22,1:37:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't congratulate yourself for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.22,1:37:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You give thanks for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.22,1:37:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you happen to make an observation that leads to great discoveries,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.22,1:37:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you're thankful.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.22,1:37:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not prideful.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.22,1:37:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thankful.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.22,1:37:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very thankful that, you know, we discovered how to discern truth from falsehood in about an instant at no cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.22,1:37:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I am very thankful to Almighty God for such a wondrous gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.32,1:37:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Have supportive relationships.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.32,1:37:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it till you make it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.32,1:37:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Be a role model.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.42,1:37:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Decide to be happy no matter what the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.42,1:37:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Great success is often fortuitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.42,1:37:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Expect the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.89,1:37:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds familiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.77,1:37:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid winning the lottery at calamity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.34,1:37:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have seen on television, I'm sure, what happens to people who win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.34,1:37:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, these multi-million, they won $13 million or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.47,1:38:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to the life of people who win the lottery is 100% calamitous.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.47,1:38:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Divorce rates, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.47,1:38:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide rates extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.47,1:38:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Drugs, accident rate.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.47,1:38:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The most calamitous thing that can happen to you is to win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.81,1:38:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody disbelieve that?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.89,1:38:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd like to try, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.18,1:38:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it has both conscious and unconscious consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.18,1:38:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the media make it even worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.18,1:38:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine how many friends you'll have if it's announced on the evening television you just won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.18,1:38:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, your mailbox is jammed like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.18,1:38:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a poor widow with five children, and I have tuberculosis, and four of my children have polio,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.18,1:38:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all living in a hogan in South America surrounded by demons,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.18,1:39:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and a small donation would mean life or death to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.46,1:39:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yours is the saddest story I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.97,1:39:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If that don't juggle some money out of you, I don't know what will.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.97,1:39:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.18,1:39:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.85,1:39:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, avoid winning the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.85,1:39:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in buying a lottery ticket because you might win it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.85,1:39:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.32,1:39:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.00,1:39:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look up the research literature on winners of the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.00,1:39:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Divorce rate 100%, suicide rate five times average, addiction and alcoholism, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.00,1:39:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.00,1:39:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The most disastrous thing that can happen to you in this world is to win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.10,1:39:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.10,1:40:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.02,1:40:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I said not buying a ticket, winning the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.02,1:40:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiots buy the tickets.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.26,1:40:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a sucker game.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.26,1:40:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the money out of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.26,1:40:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning the lottery is probably the worst thing that can happen to you in our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.26,1:40:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.67,1:40:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.67,1:40:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst thing that can happen to you in our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.85,1:40:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.85,1:40:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely and totally destructive.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.85,1:40:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And almost every single case has been studied.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.85,1:40:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It led to suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.85,1:40:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The divorce rate is about 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.85,1:40:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide rate is, I don't know, 80%.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.43,1:40:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.43,1:40:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls in energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.43,1:40:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just money, but the energy that all that pulls in.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.43,1:40:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the media attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.43,1:40:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I pray to God, dear God, please don't let me win the lottery tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.43,1:40:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.31,1:40:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep a watchful eye on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.31,1:41:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The big I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.51,1:41:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The big I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.51,1:41:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are successful, the ego tends to jump in and say, boy, aren't I wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.51,1:41:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.51,1:41:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I must be really the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.51,1:41:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep a watchful eye on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.51,1:41:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.51,1:41:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego is the narcissistic egocentricity, which is always hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.51,1:41:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The egocentricity, the ego keeps itself alive by feeding on the energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.51,1:41:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore, it's always hopeful of taking over.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.51,1:41:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Its enemy is spiritual alignment.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.51,1:41:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Its enemy, the enemy of the ego, is the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.51,1:41:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.51,1:41:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.51,1:41:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.51,1:41:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.51,1:41:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.51,1:41:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.51,1:41:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So without spirituality to balance it, the ego runs everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.93,1:41:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Runs the person's life and runs them eventually into hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.27,1:41:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.27,1:41:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So keep a watchful eye on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.27,1:41:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that the ego, the egocentricity is prideful and always looking to win.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.40,1:42:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize the world has gotten along without you thus far.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.40,1:42:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.40,1:42:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one that brings us back to reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.40,1:42:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The world has gotten along without you thus far.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.43,1:42:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell, I didn't know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.23,1:42:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize the world has gotten along without Dr. Hawkins thus far.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.38,1:42:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.38,1:42:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.98,1:42:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliminate that one from the slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.98,1:42:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is whatever you say it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.44,1:42:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Win the hula hoop.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.57,1:42:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat more hot dogs in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.57,1:42:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What people will do for publicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.34,1:42:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to remember the other day.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.53,1:42:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My memory isn't as sharp as it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.53,1:42:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the Beatles lived in a, I had an apartment on 5th.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.53,1:42:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And across the Central Park on the other side were the, oh, the Dakotas.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.53,1:42:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Two apartment buildings, the Dakotas.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.53,1:43:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the top floor of one was a psychoanalyst who I knew was a friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.53,1:43:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And he had a cat and used to walk around the edge of it and drive me crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.63,1:43:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other one was one of the Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.63,1:43:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I forget the name of this crazy guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.23,1:43:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rang the door of the Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.23,1:43:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the Beatles answered the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.23,1:43:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And he shot him dead in the chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.23,1:43:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that story?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.23,1:43:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Which Beatle was it that he got shot?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.23,1:43:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who? John?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.26,1:43:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,John Lennon.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.26,1:43:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.73,1:43:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When asked why he did it, he just wanted to be famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.96,1:43:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He shot John Lennon dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.96,1:43:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he wanted to be famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.02,1:43:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about egocentricity.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.02,1:43:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably the long time, the world winner.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.02,1:43:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet there are more crimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.02,1:43:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,More crimes reported recently of the same ilk.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.18,1:43:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine shooting somebody dead in order to be famous?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.18,1:43:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a recent story along the same lines.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.18,1:43:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget who it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.18,1:43:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But it reminded me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.18,1:44:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn't remember which Beatle it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.85,1:44:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So success is whatever you say it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.85,1:44:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot John Lennon.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.85,1:44:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Win the hula hoop contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.85,1:44:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.85,1:44:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How many hot dogs are you going to eat in ten minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.18,1:44:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.93,1:44:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the end, after all the 101 ways, of course you're going to be successful.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.01,1:44:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you realize that fame is only fame.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.46,1:44:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fame is only fame.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.46,1:44:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the magic chariot to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.46,1:44:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to fill your life with beautiful women clamoring to jump in bed with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.46,1:44:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fame is only fame.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.46,1:44:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about this thick.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.46,1:44:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fame is this fame.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.46,1:44:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's fame is tomorrow's disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.46,1:44:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the day after that's rerun.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.26,1:44:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how spectacular your life is, folks, someday you're all going to be a rerun.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.50,1:44:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Heaven have it, God has a big TV set and he pushes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.50,1:45:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And there goes your rerun on your life, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.50,1:45:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ever figure your whole life is photographed and then you put it on fast forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.50,1:45:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.02,1:45:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You put it on reverse.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.02,1:45:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.02,1:45:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you push the button the other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.02,1:45:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.02,1:45:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Say you run your life forward and you run it backward for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.02,1:45:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes it's best to just push the erase button.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.02,1:45:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That particular incident will just hit erase.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.10,1:45:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.10,1:45:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.32,1:45:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As life goes on.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.32,1:45:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to avoid the things that you have to erase later on.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.32,1:45:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's one reason to be integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.32,1:45:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to take a break and then in five minutes we're going to reconvene.
